OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F379A1779700299
OL,3,CKing surprises theatregoers at
OL,4,CShakespeare show in Warwickshire
OL,6,FMr Evans said: "When Guy Henry came
OL,7,Fon, who plays Stephano, he reached
OL,8,Fover to me and said 'Is that Guy
OL,9,FHenry?' I was just astonished at his
OL,10,Fknowledge of actors.
OL,12,F"You get the impression he's a true
OL,13,Fenthusiast of the theatre."
OL,15,FDuring the interval, the King was
OL,16,Fhanded a drink before he met the Royal
OL,17,FShakespeare Theatre's in-house costume
OL,18,Fdepartment and admired a crown used in
OL,19,Fthe company's production of Edward II
OL,20,Flast year.
OL,26,@nD@POUtD@AOUuD@[O]
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G3/7
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BC Eng News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,380,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37904
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F379A1779700299
OL,3,CKing surprises theatregoers at
OL,4,CShakespeare show in Warwickshire
OL,6,FHe also touched the fabric of a dress
OL,7,Fworn by Dame Judi Dench in All's Well
OL,8,FThat Ends Well in 2003, while he
OL,9,Fmarvelled at David Tennant's robe and
OL,10,Fgown from his role in Richard II in
OL,11,F2013 and a costume worn by Sir Antony
OL,12,FSher in a 1984 production of Richard
OL,13,FIII.
OL,15,FThe King described the costumes as
OL,16,F"brilliant".
OL,18,FHe also gave a standing ovation at the
OL,19,Fend of the performance.
OL,26,@xD@AOUxD@KO]
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G4/7
