PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F379A1779700299
OL,3,CKing surprises theatregoers at
OL,4,CShakespeare show in Warwickshire
OL,6,FCharles has been the patron of the
OL,7,FRoyal Shakespeare Theatre since 2024,
OL,8,Ffollowing in the footsteps of the late
OL,9,FQueen Elizabeth II ` who held the
OL,10,Fpatronage since the company's creation
OL,11,Fin 1961.
OL,13,FSir Kenneth is playing the role of the
OL,14,Fexiled Duke of Milan, Prospero, for
OL,15,Fthe first time in his career, which
OL,16,Fhas included 35 Shakespeare
OL,17,Fproductions.
OL,19,FThe Tempest, which was one of the last
OL,20,Fplays written by Shakespeare, is
OL,21,Frunning at the theatre until June 20.
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G5/7
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
